    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin adds user signature support to bbPress 2.0 and above. Currently support have been added for BuddyPress installations as well which have site wide forums enabled.<\/p>\n<p>Currently, users are supported with:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Maximum length of 500 charactors in the user edit page for the signature.<\/li>\n<li>User signature for topics and replies.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to add bbcodes support to the user signature, you might want to install <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/extend\/plugins\/bbpress-bbcode\/\" rel=\"ugc\">bbPress2 BBCode<\/a> plugin. Output from bbcode plugin is in screenshot 3.<br \/>\nNote: Requires the <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/extend\/plugins\/bbpress\/\" rel=\"ugc\">bbPress plugin<\/a> to be installed.<\/p>\n<h4>Donate<\/h4>\n<p>You may donate by going <a href=\"http:\/\/www.rewweb.co.uk\/donate\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h4>Todo<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Options page<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Place &#8216;bbp-signature&#8217; folder in your plugins directory.<\/li>\n<li>Activate bbP Signature.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>If you are trying to activate user signature on top of BuddyPress installation,<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Enable site wide forums.<\/li>\n<li>Add a profile field with name &#8220;Signature&#8221;. (Profile field name should be correct for the functioning of the plugin).<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h4>Optional<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/extend\/plugins\/bbpress-bbcode\/\" rel=\"ugc\">bbPress2 BBCode<\/a> plugin for bbcode support in User signature.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='what%20is%20required%20to%20run%20this%3F'>\nWhat is required to run this?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>You should be running WordPress 3.1+ and <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/extend\/plugins\/bbpress\/\" rel=\"ugc\">bbPress<\/a> 2.0 +.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.3 (08-02-2021)<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>removed revision filter as was causing double display of revisions<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.1 (29-08-2012)<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added BuddyPress support.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0 (20-10-2011)<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug fixes and supports latest version of bbPress and WordPress<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>0.1 beta (18-04-2011)<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial Release<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
